All that happens is a leading edge pops back and gives Elliott and New Zealand their first wicket of the day

commentary: Wheeler to Rossouw, 2 runs leading edge lobs point, and there is a run-out chance as well. Loads of things happening all at once, and this is so so tight. The stymps are disturbed, but the bail takes an awful time to be dislodged. Amid that, the batsman despite a dive is still on the line. This might head into the old 'inconclusive' and 'benefit of the doubt to the batsman' area. Good ball too, gets extra bounce which makes his intended on-the-up drive take an edge and leap over point. Then deep third man comes into play, as does the SA batsmens greed in stealing a second. All is well for the hosts

commentary: Rabada to Williamson, 1 run dropped by Miller. What is going on in this series? Two of the best units making silly mistakes. He seemed to have it all under control, running in from deep midwicket, got two hands to it as he goes in for the slide, and then it just pops out. Did he lose it in the crowd? commentary: Behardien to Williamson, 2 runs oooh, has it worked? Almost. I wonder if Steyn has misjudged this catch. It was a steepler, and he was tracking it over his shoulder while running towards the long-off boundary. KW had mistimed the lift, and it went a little too high instead of long. But the fielder moved to his right, instead of towards the left where the ball was heading and ends up not being able to reach it
